  {
    "id": 38,
    "key": "8DWIHVKV",
    "title": "Kinetics of fission-gas-bubble-nucleated void swelling of the alpha-uranium phase of irradiated U-Zr and U-Pu-Zr fuel",
    "date": "1993-00-00 1993",
    "journal": "Journal of Nuclear Materials",
    "doi": "10.1016/0022-3115(93)90261-V",
    "abstract": "Bias-driven growth of voids is identified as a major swelling mechanism in the α-uranium phase of irradiated U-Pu-Zr metal fuels being developed at Argonne National Laboratory for the Integral Fast Reactor (IFR). The trends in U-Pu-Zr swelling data prior to fuel/cladding contact can be interpreted in terms of unrestrained void swelling. It is theorized that the swelling mechanisms at work in the α-uranium phase can be modeled by single-vacancy and single-interstitial kinetics, thus avoiding the ",
    "pdf_path": "/Volumes/openclaw记忆/Zotero_storage/storage/Q7B3KBIA/Rest_1993_Kinetics of fission-gas-bubble-nucleated void swelling of the alpha-uranium phase of irradiated U-Zr and U-Pu-Zr fuel.pdf",
