    "id": 5796,
    "key": "T5R7GFDA",
    "title": "Thermal treatment of uranium oxide irradiated in pressurized water reactor: Swelling and release of fission gases",
    "date": "1998-06-01 1998-06-01",
    "journal": "Journal of Nuclear Materials",
    "doi": "10.1016/S0022-3115(98)00039-7",
    "abstract": "Unstressed samples of uranium oxide taken from pressurized water reactor (PWR) fuel after two normal operating cycles, i.e., with a burn-up of 25 GWd/tU, were subjected to thermal treatment in a laboratory furnace at temperatures between 1130°C and 1715°C for durations between 5 min and 10 h. The variation of the quantity of fission gas released over time was determined at each temperature. The experimental results were found to compare with those of an existing numerical model, and it would thu",
